"{\"uid\": \"theatlantic.com-books-archive-2024-07-olympics-paris-books-history-recommendations-679245\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"These titles will allow you to view the competition with a new appreciation.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 76, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These titles\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 12}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 36, \"to\": 51}, {\"ngram\": \"a new appreciation\", \"from\": 57, \"to\": 75}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This week,11 million touristswill join more than10,000 athletesfrom 206 countries for the 2024 Summer Olympics.Fifty-nine percentof American adults say they plan to tune in to the Games.\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 210, \"end\": 218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3184050493277264e-13, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This week,11 million touristswill\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 111}, {\"ngram\": \"206 countries\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 159}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 164, \"to\": 188}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a level of attention that the founders of the modern Olympics could only have dreamed of achieving.\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a level\", \"from\": 273, \"to\": 280}, {\"ngram\": \"attention\", \"from\": 284, \"to\": 293}, {\"ngram\": \"the founders\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 311}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympics\", \"from\": 315, \"to\": 334}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games did not debut to much fanfare: When a Harvard track athlete tried to get permission to compete in the first modern edition, in 1896, a skeptical dean accused him of wanting \\\"to go to Athens on a junket.\\\"\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 421, \"end\": 428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.47759357235933e-15, \"text\": \"Harvard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harvard_University\"}, {\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 2.6922619579317653e-11, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Games\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 382}, {\"ngram\": \"much fanfare\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"permission\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 466}, {\"ngram\": \"the first modern edition\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 505}, {\"ngram\": \"a skeptical dean\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 532}, {\"ngram\": \"a junket\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even the well-known phrasesOlympic recordandOlympic championdidn't enter the popular lexicon until the 1920s.\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 696, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Even the well-known phrasesOlympic recordandOlympic\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 638}, {\"ngram\": \"championdidn't\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 653}, {\"ngram\": \"the popular lexicon\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 679}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the 20th century, the Olympic Games quickly transformed from little-known curiosities to major, world-altering events.\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 20th century\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 740}, {\"ngram\": \"little-known curiosities\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 790}, {\"ngram\": \"major, world-altering events\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 822}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While writing my book,The Other Olympians: Fascism, Queerness, and the Making of Modern Sports, I was struck by how much the Games have shaped contemporary life and politics.\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 998, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my book\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 845}, {\"ngram\": \"The Other Olympians\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 865}, {\"ngram\": \"Fascism\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"Queerness\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 885}, {\"ngram\": \"the Making\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"Modern Sports\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 918}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 954}, {\"ngram\": \"contemporary life\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 984}, {\"ngram\": \"politics\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 997}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These maddening, wondrous competitions have been the site of terrorism and protest, triumph and perseverance, political victory and corruption, and have influenced which states we count as countries and which cities become tourism hubs.\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1235, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These maddening, wondrous competitions\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"terrorism\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1069}, {\"ngram\": \"protest\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1081}, {\"ngram\": \"triumph\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"perseverance\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"political victory\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1126}, {\"ngram\": \"corruption\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"countries\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1197}, {\"ngram\": \"which cities\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"tourism hubs\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1234}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Understanding the Games' spasmodic path to their current place in the monoculture, and their immense power, allows you to watch these sports with a new appreciation for the backroom decisions that make them possible.\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1453, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games' spasmodic path\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1276}, {\"ngram\": \"their current place\", \"from\": 1280, \"to\": 1299}, {\"ngram\": \"the monoculture\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1318}, {\"ngram\": \"these sports\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1377}, {\"ngram\": \"a new appreciation\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"the backroom decisions\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1428}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are seven essential books to complement your viewing.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1512, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"seven essential books\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1484}, {\"ngram\": \"your viewing\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dreamers and Schemers: How an Improbable Bid for the 1932 Olympics Transformed Los Angeles From Dusty Outpost to Global Metropolis, by Barry Siegel On paper, the first Olympics in Los Angeles, held in 1932, probably should not have happened.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1593, \"end\": 1604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4980506829916688e-31, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1634, \"end\": 1644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metropolis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.155437875362567e-18, \"text\": \"Metropolis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metropolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metropolis\"}, {\"begin\": 1649, \"end\": 1654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"score\": 0.9999783403817816, \"rank\": 2.1660086697298154e-05, \"text\": \"Barry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\"}, {\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4980506829916688e-31, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dreamers\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1522}, {\"ngram\": \"Schemers\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1535}, {\"ngram\": \"How an Improbable Bid\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1558}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1932 Olympics\", \"from\": 1563, \"to\": 1580}, {\"ngram\": \"Dusty Outpost\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"paper\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1670}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Olympics\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1690}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 1920s and early '30s, the city was seedy and unstable, rife with political corruption and mysterious deaths, and had little worldwide reputation.\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1909, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"early '\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"30s\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1784}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1794}, {\"ngram\": \"political corruption\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"mysterious deaths\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"little worldwide reputation\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1908}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most inauspiciously, the Games unfolded during the height of the Great Depression.\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1992, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1940}, {\"ngram\": \"the height\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1967}, {\"ngram\": \"the Great Depression\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 1991}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the state of California decided to subsidize some of the event's costs amid mass unemployment, workers protested with signs that readGroceries Not Games!\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\":