": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joan_Crawford\"}, {\"begin\": 2452, \"end\": 2465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norma_Shearer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Norma Shearer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norma_Shearer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norma_Shearer\"}, {\"begin\": 2475, \"end\": 2482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Chaplin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.271624615764956e-29, \"text\": \"Chaplin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Chaplin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlie_Chaplin\"}, {\"begin\": 2488, \"end\": 2497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clara_Bow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Clara Bow\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clara_Bow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clara_Bow\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Siegel\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2226}, {\"ngram\": \"the making\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2248}, {\"ngram\": \"this Olympics\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"this city\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2302}, {\"ngram\": \"impressively sequenced detail\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2335}, {\"ngram\": \"the-scenes\", \"from\": 2360, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 2402, \"to\": 2410}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2518}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, studios hosted lunches and an exclusive beach-house party, and 30,000 palm trees were planted across the city to give it the air of paradise.\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2672, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"studios\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2538}, {\"ngram\": \"lunches\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2553}, {\"ngram\": \"an exclusive beach-house party\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2588}, {\"ngram\": \"30,000 palm trees\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2611}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2640}, {\"ngram\": \"the air\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2659}, {\"ngram\": \"paradise\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the closing ceremonies, Los Angeles had a new halo.\", \"from\": 2673, \"to\": 2727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2700, \"end\": 2711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4980506829916688e-31, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremonies\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2698}, {\"ngram\": \"a new halo\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics had proved-for the first time, but not the last-that wherever they went, the eyes of the world followed.\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2740}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2770}, {\"ngram\": \"the eyes\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 2822}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2826, \"to\": 2835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games Must Go On: Avery Brundage and the Olympic Movement, by Allen Guttmann The modern Olympics are hard to understand without first understanding Avery Brundage, an American athlete, a Chicago real-estate developer, and, later, president of the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 3131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2869, \"end\": 2883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avery_Brundage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Avery Brundage\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avery_Brundage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avery_Brundage\"}, {\"begin\": 2892, \"end\": 2908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9841547827838213, \"rank\": 0.016100330449202928, \"text\": \"Olympic Movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2913, \"end\": 2918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_L._Allen\", \"score\": 0.9999958074555828, \"rank\": 4.192555237023322e-06, \"text\": \"Allen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_L._Allen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_L._Allen\"}, {\"begin\": 3019, \"end\": 3027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3184050493277264e-13, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3039, \"end\": 3046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.476015760854517e-14, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}, {\"begin\": 3099, \"end\": 3130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Games\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2856}, {\"ngram\": \"The modern Olympics\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 2947}, {\"ngram\": \"Avery Brundage\", \"from\": 2999, \"to\": 3013}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His style was brash: He wasn't afraid to ban a top competitor, or to wave away the need for women's sports.\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3239, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His style\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3141}, {\"ngram\": \"a top competitor\", \"from\": 3177, \"to\": 3193}, {\"ngram\": \"the need\", \"from\": 3211, \"to\": 3219}, {\"ngram\": \"women's sports\", \"from\": 3224, \"to\": 3238}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, as Guttmann argues in his definitive biography of this morally complicated man, perhaps no one shaped the governance of the Olympics more.\", \"from\": 3240, \"to\": 3383, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Guttmann\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3256}, {\"ngram\": \"his definitive biography\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3291}, {\"ngram\": \"this morally complicated man\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3323}, {\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 3333, \"to\": 3339}, {\"ngram\": \"the governance\", \"from\": 3347, \"to\": 3361}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3377}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brundage helped turn the Olympics-once a clubby, largely European affair-into a truly global institution.\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 3489, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brundage\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 3392}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3417}, {\"ngram\": \"a truly global institution\", \"from\": 3462, \"to\": 3488}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was an early advocate of expansion, pushing for a Japan-hosted Olympics in 1940 (though those Games were canceled because of the war).\", \"from\": 3490, \"to\": 3627, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an early advocate\", \"from\": 3497, \"to\": 3514}, {\"ngram\": \"expansion\", \"from\": 3518, \"to\": 3527}, {\"ngram\": \"a Japan-hosted Olympics\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3564}, {\"ngram\": \"those Games\", \"from\": 3581, \"to\": 3592}, {\"ngram\": \"the war\", \"from\": 3618, \"to\": 3625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He helped persuade the U.S.S.R. to participate for the first time, instituted the first anti-doping controls, and cemented the sex-testing policies that would shape who was allowed to compete in women's sports for decades to come.\", \"from\": 3628, \"to\": 3858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3651, \"end\": 3659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.103705493734508e-22, \"text\": \"U.S.S.R.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 3679, \"to\": 3693}, {\"ngram\": \"the first anti-doping controls\", \"from\": 3706, \"to\": 3736}, {\"ngram\": \"the sex-testing policies\", \"from\": 3751, \"to\": 3775}, {\"ngram\": \"women's sports\", \"from\": 3823, \"to\": 3837}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 3842, \"to\": 3849}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brundage also solidified the IOC's generally agnostic relationship with world politics.\", \"from\": 3859, \"to\": 3946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3888, \"end\": 3891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6076375741895887e-66, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brundage\", \"from\": 3859, \"to\": 3867}, {\"ngram\": \"world politics\", \"from\": 3931, \"to\": 3945}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He saw no issue with allowing the Nazis to host the Olympics in 1936, writing that the Olympics must not get involved in politics.\", \"from\": 3947, \"to\": 4077, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3981, \"end\": 3986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"score\": 0.9999815752149783, \"rank\": 1.536355946012836e-05, \"text\": \"Nazis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no issue\", \"from\": 3954, \"to\": 3962}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3995, \"to\": 4007}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4030, \"to\": 4042}, {\"ngram\": \"politics\", \"from\": 4068, \"to\": 4076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Years later, as leader of the IOC, Brundage stuck to those beliefs: In the 1960s, after the United Nations tried to ban apartheid South Africa from competing, Brundage pushed to allow the country to participate anyway.\", \"from\": 4078, \"to\": 4296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4108, \"end\": 4111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6076375741895887e-66, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4170, \"end\": 4184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.416839994259209e-14, \"text\": \"United Nations\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}, {\"begin\": 4208, \"end\": 4220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0929086239307973e-14, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"leader\", \"from\": 4094, \"to\": 4100}, {\"ngram\": \"Brundage\", \"from\": 4113, \"to\": 4121}, {\"ngram\": \"those beliefs\", \"from\": 4131, \"to\": 4144}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1960s\", \"from\": 4149, \"to\": 4158}, {\"ngram\": \"Brundage\", \"from\": 4237, \"to\": 4245}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 4262, \"to\": 4273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Guttmann untangles Brundage's many failures all while acknowledging that, for better or worse, he is the reason the Olympic Games exist as they do today.\", \"from\": 4297, \"to\": 4450, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Guttmann\", \"from\": 4297, \"to\": 4305}, {\"ngram\": \"Brundage's many failures\", \"from\": 4316, \"to\": 4340}, {\"ngram\": \"the reason\", \"from\": 4398, \"to\": 4408}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 4409, \"to\": 4426}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read: How skateboarding at the Olympics stayed rebellious Make It Count, by CeC\\u00e9 Telfer If not for a new eligibility policy, CeC\\u00e9 Telfer-a Jamaica-born hurdler and former college athlete who won the NCAA title in the 400 meters in 2019-might be competing in Paris this year.\", \"from\": 4452, \"to\": 4728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4653, \"end\": 4657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 5.3766754463323066e-11, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 4712, \"end\": 4717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1489192744361675e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Read\", \"from\": 4452, \"to\": 4456}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4491}, {\"ngram\": \"CeC\\u00e9 Telfer\", \"from\": 4528, \"to\": 4539}, {\"ngram\": \"a new eligibility policy\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4575}, {\"ngram\": \"CeC\\u00e9 Telfer\", \"from\": 4577, \"to\": 4588}, {\"ngram\": \"a Jamaica-born hurdler\", \"from\": 4589, \"to\": 4611}, {\"ngram\": \"former college athlete\", \"from\": 4616, \"to\": 4638}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400 meters\", \"from\": 4665, \"to\": 4679}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In her new memoir, Telfer, who is trans, chronicles her rise through track-and-field sports, including her repeated, grueling efforts to try out for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 4729, \"to\": 4891, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her new memoir\", \"from\": 4732, \"to\": 4746}, {\"ngram\": \"Telfer\", \"from\": 4748, \"to\": 4754}, {\"ngram\": \"trans\", \"from\": 4763, \"to\": 4768}, {\"ngram\": \"her rise\", \"from\": 4781, \"to\": 4789}, {\"ngram\": \"track-and-field sports\", \"from\": 4798, \"to\": 4820}, {\"ngram\": \"her repeated, grueling efforts\", \"from\": 4832, \"to\": 4862}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4878, \"to\": 4890}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While she was readying herself for Tokyo in 2021, Telfer struggled with homelessness, and picked up extra shifts at her nursing-home job.\", \"from\": 4892, \"to\": 5029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4927, \"end\": 4932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9985422998433595, \"rank\": 0.0014598281486124627, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Telfer\", \"from\": 4942, \"to\": 4948}, {\"ngram\": \"homelessness\", \"from\": 4964, \"to\": 4976}, {\"ngram\": \"extra shifts\", \"from\": 4992, \"to\": 5004}, {\"ngram\": \"her nursing-home job\", \"from\": 5008, \"to\": 5028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She needed money, she needed to train, and she needed to meet with doctors to ensure she was keeping her hormone levels within the range required at the time for trans women to compete-\\\"I never get a break,\\\" she writes of the period.\", \"from\": 5030, \"to\": 5263, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 5041, \"to\": 5046}, {\"ngram\": \"doctors\", \"from\": 5097, \"to\": 5104}, {\"ngram\": \"her hormone levels\", \"from\": 5131, \"to\": 5149}, {\"ngram\": \"the range\", \"from\": 5157, \"to\": 5166}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 5179, \"to\": 5187}, {\"ngram\": \"trans\", \"from\": 5192, \"to\": 5197}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5198, \"to\": 5203}, {\"ngram\": \"compete-\\\"I\", \"from\": 5207, \"to\": 5217}, {\"ngram\": \"a break\", \"from\": 5228, \"to\": 5235}, {\"ngram\": \"the period\", \"from\": 5252, \"to\": 5262}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet the day before she was supposed to fly to Oregon for the Olympic trials, she was notified that she needed to submit additional documentation-therapy notes, more hormone tests, reformatted blood work-only to then be barred from running by USA Track & Field that night.\", \"from\": 5264, \"to\": 5535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5310, \"end\": 5316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"score\": 0.8506962250012141, \"rank\": 0.1755077436700324, \"text\": \"Oregon\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic trials\", \"from\": 5321, \"to\": 5339}, {\"ngram\": \"additional documentation-therapy notes\", \"from\": 5384, \"to\": 5422}, {\"ngram\": \"more hormone tests\", \"from\": 5424, \"to\": 5442}, {\"ngram\": \"blood work\", \"from\": 5456, \"to\": 5466}, {\"ngram\": \"USA Track\", \"from\": 5506, \"to\": 5515}, {\"ngram\": \"Field\", \"from\": 5518, \"to\": 5523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Devastated, Telfer turned her attention to the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 5536, \"to\": 5598, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Telfer\", \"from\": 5548, \"to\": 5554}, {\"ngram\": \"her attention\", \"from\": 5562, \"to\": 5575}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 5579, \"to\": 5597}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, in early 2023, she got word that World Athletics, the governing body for track-and-field sports, had changed its standard.\", \"from\": 5599, \"to\": 5727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5638, \"end\": 5653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.39245518679329e-32, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"word\", \"from\": 5628, \"to\": 5632}, {\"ngram\": \"the governing body\", \"from\": 5655, \"to\": 5673}, {\"ngram\": \"track-and-field sports\", \"from\": 5678, \"to\": 5700}, {\"ngram\": \"its standard\", \"from\": 5714, \"to\": 5726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now trans women are essentially banned from the Olympics.\", \"from\": 5728, \"to\": 5785, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5738, \"to\": 5743}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5772, \"to\": 5784}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Telfer's memoir focuses on her personal journey, and spends much time on her hopes, dreams, and years of assiduous training, but many of the scenes she describes-such as waiting for the global federation to release its new policy, her future hanging on the wording of one subjectively written statement-underscore the very human ramifications of Olympic bureaucracy.\", \"from\": 5786, \"to\": 6152, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Telfer's memoir\", \"from\": 5786, \"to\": 5801}, {\"ngram\": \"her personal journey\", \"from\": 5813, \"to\": 5833}, {\"ngram\": \"much time\", \"from\": 5846, \"to\": 5855}, {\"ngram\": \"her hopes\", \"from\": 5859, \"to\": 5868}, {\"ngram\": \"dreams\", \"from\": 5870, \"to\": 5876}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 5882, \"to\": 5887}, {\"ngram\": \"assiduous training\", \"from\": 5891, \"to\": 5909}, {\"ngram\": \"the scenes\", \"from\": 5923, \"to\": 5933}, {\"ngram\": \"the global federation\", \"from\": 5968, \"to\": 5989}, {\"ngram\": \"its new policy\", \"from\": 6001, \"to\": 6015}, {\"ngram\": \"her future\", \"from\": 6017, \"to\": 6027}, {\"ngram\": \"the wording\", \"from\": 6039, \"to\": 6050}, {\"ngram\": \"the very human ramifications\", \"from\": 6100, \"to\": 6128}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic bureaucracy\", \"from\": 6132, \"to\": 6151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Power Games: A Political History of the Olympics, by Jules Boykoff The televised spectacle of the Olympics tends to hide some of the Games' most crucial logistics: who gets to compete, which countries are allowed to host or send teams, and even which workers built the stadiums.\", \"from\": 6156, \"to\": 6435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6209, \"end\": 6222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jules Boykoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Power Games\", \"from\": 6156, \"to\": 6167}, {\"ngram\": \"A Political History\", \"from\": 6169, \"to\": 6188}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6192, \"to\": 6204}, {\"ngram\": \"The televised spectacle\", \"from\": 6223, \"to\": 6246}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6250, \"to\": 6262}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' most crucial logistics\", \"from\": 6285, \"to\": 6318}, {\"ngram\": \"which countries\", \"from\": 6341, \"to\": 6356}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 6385, \"to\": 6390}, {\"ngram\": \"even which\", \"from\": 6396, \"to\": 6406}, {\"ngram\": \"workers\", \"from\": 6407, \"to\": 6414}, {\"ngram\": \"the stadiums\", \"from\": 6421, \"to\": 6433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boykoff brings this secret side of the Olympics to life inPower Games, a masterful chronicle of the bureaucracy behind the event.\", \"from\": 6436, \"to\": 6565, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Boykoff\", \"from\": 6436, \"to\": 6443}, {\"ngram\": \"this secret side\", \"from\": 6451, \"to\": 6467}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6471, \"to\": 6483}, {\"ngram\": \"life inPower Games\", \"from\": 6487, \"to\": 6505}, {\"ngram\": \"a masterful chronicle\", \"from\": 6507, \"to\": 6528}, {\"ngram\": \"the bureaucracy\", \"from\": 6532, \"to\": 6547}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 6555, \"to\": 6564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boykoff starts with Pierre de Coubertin, the French baron who jump-started the Olympics in 1896 and who saw them as, almost exclusively, a venue for white men; he then takes readers on a wild jaunt through administrative history.\", \"from\": 6566, \"to\": 6795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6586, \"end\": 6605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}, {\"begin\": 6611, \"end\": 6617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7407582209703885, \"rank\": 0.3479851939015537, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Boykoff\", \"from\": 6566, \"to\": 6573}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6641, \"to\": 6653}, {\"ngram\": \"white men\", \"from\": 6715, \"to\": 6724}, {\"ngram\": \"readers\", \"from\": 6740, \"to\": 6747}, {\"ngram\": \"a wild jaunt\", \"from\": 6751, \"to\": 6763}, {\"ngram\": \"administrative history\", \"from\": 6772, \"to\": 6794}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We meet officials such as Avery Brundage, of course, as well as Alice Milliat, a stenographer who created her own rival to the Olympics called the Women's World Games.\", \"from\": 6796, \"to\": 6963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6822, \"end\": 6836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avery_Brundage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Avery Brundage\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avery_Brundage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avery_Brundage\"}, {\"begin\": 6860, \"end\": 6873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Milliat\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alice Milliat\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Milliat\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Milliat\"}, {\"begin\": 6951, \"end\": 6962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6965703896975182e-15, \"text\": \"World Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 6804, \"to\": 6813}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 6841, \"to\": 6847}, {\"ngram\": \"a stenographer\", \"from\": 6875, \"to\": 6889}, {\"ngram\": \"her own rival\", \"from\": 6902, \"to\": 6915}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6919, \"to\": 6931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boykoff is particularly sharp when discussing the activists who have rallied against the Olympics.\", \"from\": 6964, \"to\": 7062, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Boykoff\", \"from\": 6964, \"to\": 6971}, {\"ngram\": \"the activists\", \"from\": 7010, \"to\": 7023}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 7049, \"to\": 7061}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Denver was awarded the 1976 Winter edition, for instance, locals staged letter-writing campaigns arguing that the Games would have a devastating ecological impact.\", \"from\": 7063, \"to\": 7231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7068, \"end\": 7074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3592305459827594e-24, \"text\": \"Denver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denver\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1976 Winter edition\", \"from\": 7087, \"to\": 7110}, {\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 7116, \"to\": 7124}, {\"ngram\": \"locals\", \"from\": 7126, \"to\": 7132}, {\"ngram\": \"letter-writing campaigns\", \"from\": 7140, \"to\": 7164}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 7178, \"to\": 7187}, {\"ngram\": \"a devastating ecological impact\", \"from\": 7199, \"to\": 7230}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They succeeded in securing a ballot referendum against using public money for the event-and they won.\", \"from\": 7232, \"to\": 7333, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a ballot referendum\", \"from\": 7259, \"to\": 7278}, {\"ngram\": \"public money\", \"from\": 7293, \"to\": 7305}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 7310, \"to\": 7319}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without subsidies to keep it in Denver, 1976's Games were moved to Innsbruck, Austria, instead.\", \"from\": 7334, \"to\": 7429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7366, \"end\": 7372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3592305459827594e-24, \"text\": \"Denver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denver\"}, {\"begin\": 7401, \"end\": 7410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Innsbruck\", \"score\": 0.999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.747296802266046e-11, \"text\": \"Innsbruck\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Innsbruck\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Innsbruck\"}, {\"begin\": 7412, \"end\": 7419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"score\": 0.9957982515198278, \"rank\": 0.004208960824878804, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"subsidies\", \"from\": 7342, \"to\": 7351}, {\"ngram\": \"1976's Games\", \"from\": 7374, \"to\": 7386}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those stories feel particularly resonant as the NOlympics movement to cancel the Olympics gains steam inLos Angeles, the 2028 host.\", \"from\": 7430, \"to\": 7561, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Those stories\", \"from\": 7430, \"to\": 7443}, {\"ngram\": \"the NOlympics movement\", \"from\": 7474, \"to\": 7496}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics gains steam inLos Angeles\", \"from\": 7507, \"to\": 7545}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 host\", \"from\": 7547, \"to\": 7560}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read: The Olympics have lost their appeal Triumph:The Untold Story of Jesse Owens and Hitler's Olympics, by Jeremy Schaap Born in Alabama in 1913 to a family of sharecroppers, Jesse Owens ran track in an era when the world's top runners were athletic celebrities on par with the titans of football and baseball, Schaap writes.\", \"from\": 7563, \"to\": 7891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7634, \"end\": 7645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8068689690928404e-88, \"text\": \"Jesse Owens\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\"}, {\"begin\": 7650, \"end\": 7656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.3208974437802185e-28, \"text\": \"Hitler\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\"}, {\"begin\": 7672, \"end\": 7685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Schaap\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeremy Schaap\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Schaap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Schaap\"}, {\"begin\": 7695, \"end\": 7702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alabama\", \"score\": 0.8806726077667805, \"rank\": 0.13549574622016253, \"text\": \"Alabama\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alabama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alabama\"}, {\"begin\": 7741, \"end\": 7752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8068689690928404e-88, \"text\": \"Jesse Owens\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesse_Owens\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 7569, \"to\": 7581}, {\"ngram\": \"their appeal\", \"from\": 7592, \"to\": 7604}, {\"ngram\": \"The Untold Story\", \"from\": 7613, \"to\": 7629}, {\"ngram\": \"a family\", \"from\": 7712, \"to\": 7720}, {\"ngram\": \"sharecroppers\", \"from\": 7724, \"to\": 7737}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 7755, \"to\": 7760}, {\"ngram\": \"an era\", \"from\": 7764, \"to\": 7770}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's top runners\", \"from\": 7776, \"to\": 7799}, {\"ngram\": \"athletic celebrities\", \"from\": 7805, \"to\": 7825}, {\"ngram\": \"par\", \"from\": 7829, \"to\": 7832}, {\"ngram\": \"the titans\", \"from\": 7838, \"to\": 7848}, {\"ngram\": \"football\", \"from\": 7852, \"to\": 7860}, {\"ngram\": \"baseball\", \"from\": 7865, \"to\": 7873}, {\"ngram\": \"Schaap\", \"from\": 7875, \"to\": 7881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports officials-almost all of whom were white men-doubted Owens at every turn.\", \"from\": 7892, \"to\": 7971, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sports officials\", \"from\": 7892, \"to\": 7908}, {\"ngram\": \"almost all\", \"from\": 7909, \"to\": 7919}, {\"ngram\": \"white men-doubted Owens\", \"from\": 7933, \"to\": 7956}, {\"ngram\": \"every turn\", \"from\": 7960, \"to\": 7970}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were, of course, dead wrong: At the 1936 Berlin Games, Owens took home four gold medals.\", \"from\": 7972, \"to\": 8065, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 7986, \"to\": 7992}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1936 Berlin Games\", \"from\": 8009, \"to\": 8030}, {\"ngram\": \"Owens\", \"from\": 8032, \"to\": 8037}, {\"ngram\": \"four gold medals\", \"from\": 8048, \"to\": 8064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps the most fascinating thread inTriumph, however, centers on Owens's conflicted relationship with that year's Olympics.\", \"from\": 8066, \"to\": 8191, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Perhaps the most fascinating thread inTriumph\", \"from\": 8066, \"to\": 8111}, {\"ngram\": \", however, centers\", \"from\": 8111, \"to\": 8129}, {\"ngram\": \"Owens's conflicted relationship\", \"from\": 8133, \"to\": 8164}, {\"ngram\": \"that year's Olympics\", \"from\": 8170, \"to\": 8190}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the U.S., competing in an event that might burnish the reputation of the Nazis was controversial, and anti-fascist activists organized a massive boycott of the Games.\", \"from\": 8192, \"to\": 8361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8268, \"end\": 8273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"score\": 0.9999815752149783, \"rank\": 1.536355946012836e-05, \"text\": \"Nazis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 8195, \"to\": 8203}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 8218, \"to\": 8226}, {\"ngram\": \"the reputation\", \"from\": 8246, \"to\": 8260}, {\"ngram\": \"controversial, and anti-fascist activists\", \"from\": 8278, \"to\": 8319}, {\"ngram\": \"a massive boycott\", \"from\": 8330, \"to\": 8347}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 8351, \"to\": 8360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many American sports officials wanted Owens to come out against the protest; NAACP Secretary Walter White urged him to support it.\", \"from\": 8362, \"to\": 8492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8367, \"end\": 8375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3184050493277264e-13, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 8439, \"end\": 8444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NAACP\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.075667637909624e-26, \"text\": \"NAACP\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NAACP\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NAACP\"}, {\"begin\": 8455, \"end\": 8467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Francis_White\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.645223513180325e-71, \"text\": \"Walter White\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Francis_White\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Francis_White\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Owens\", \"from\": 8400, \"to\": 8405}, {\"ngram\": \"the protest\", \"from\": 8426, \"to\": 8437}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Owens, who personally knew the depths of America's anti-Black racism, was torn.\", \"from\": 8493, \"to\": 8572, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Owens\", \"from\": 8493, \"to\": 8498}, {\"ngram\": \"the depths\", \"from\": 8520, \"to\": 8530}, {\"ngram\": \"America's anti-Black racism\", \"from\": 8534, \"to\": 8561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At one point, he signed a letter supporting the Olympics.\", \"from\": 8573, \"to\": 8630, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one point\", \"from\": 8576, \"to\": 8585}, {\"ngram\": \"a letter\", \"from\": 8597, \"to\": 8605}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 8617, \"to\": 8629}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, in a radio interview, he seemed leery: \\\"If there is discrimination against minorities in Germany, then we must withdraw.\\\"\", \"from\": 8631, \"to\": 8758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8726, \"end\": 8733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weimar_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9555352827633802, \"rank\": 0.04650065741495307, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weimar_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weimar_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a radio interview\", \"from\": 8640, \"to\": 8657}, {\"ngram\": \"discrimination\", \"from\": 8689, \"to\": 8703}, {\"ngram\": \"minorities\", \"from\": 8712, \"to\": 8722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a weighty quandary to place on a 22-year-old athlete, and it has not gone away.\", \"from\": 8759, \"to\": 8845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a weighty quandary\", \"from\": 8766, \"to\": 8784}, {\"ngram\": \"a 22-year-old athlete\", \"from\": 8797, \"to\": 8818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, young Palestinian and South Sudanese athletes, for instance, carry the weight of competing at an elite level while also calling attention to what their communities are facing.\", \"from\": 8846, \"to\": 9028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8859, \"end\": 8870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999790427331936, \"rank\": 2.075432436111966e-05, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 8875, \"end\": 8889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Sudan\", \"score\": 0.9999999994151949, \"rank\": 5.85139112992508e-10, \"text\": \"South Sudanese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Sudan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Sudan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 8904, \"to\": 8912}, {\"ngram\": \"the weight\", \"from\": 8920, \"to\": 8930}, {\"ngram\": \"an elite level\", \"from\": 8947, \"to\": 8961}, {\"ngram\": \"attention\", \"from\": 8981, \"to\": 8990}, {\"ngram\": \"their communities\", \"from\": 8999, \"to\": 9016}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Serving Herself: The Life and Times of Althea Gibson, by Ashley Brown In 1983, a writer met with one of the most famous tennis players of her generation: Althea Gibson, the winner of 11 Grand Slam titles in the 1950s and the first Black woman to win a Grand Slam event.\", \"from\": 9030, \"to\": 9300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9069, \"end\": 9082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Althea_Gibson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Althea Gibson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Althea_Gibson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Althea_Gibson\"}, {\"begin\": 9087, \"end\": 9099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashley_Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5355961701072615e-26, \"text\": \"Ashley Brown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashley_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashley_Brown\"}, {\"begin\": 9185, \"end\": 9198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Althea_Gibson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Althea Gibson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Althea_Gibson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Althea_Gibson\"}, {\"begin\": 9289, \"end\": 9293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poetry_slam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.645309019474289e-26, \"text\": \"Slam\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poetry_slam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poetry_slam\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Life\", \"from\": 9047, \"to\": 9055}, {\"ngram\": \"Times\", \"from\": 9060, \"to\": 9065}, {\"ngram\": \"a writer\", \"from\": 9109, \"to\": 9117}, {\"ngram\": \"the most famous tennis players\", \"from\": 9134, \"to\": 9164}, {\"ngram\": \"her generation\", \"from\": 9168, \"to\": 9182}, {\"ngram\": \"the winner\", \"from\": 9199, \"to\": 9209}, {\"ngram\": \"11 Grand Slam titles\", \"from\": 9213, \"to\": 9233}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1950s\", \"from\": 9237, \"to\": 9246}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Black woman\", \"from\": 9251, \"to\": 9272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Gibson, now nearly 60, was still struggling to make ends meet.\", \"from\": 9301, \"to\": 9367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9305, \"end\": 9311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\", \"score\": 0.9961010244449675, \"rank\": 0.003914237070065629, \"text\": \"Gibson\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ends\", \"from\": 9357, \"to\": 9361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How did this happen?\", \"from\": 9368, \"to\": 9388, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In this remarkable biography, Brown presents a compelling answer: Gibson was living out \\\"the consequences of having never fit neatly into society when she was younger.\\\"\", \"from\": 9389, \"to\": 9557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9455, \"end\": 9461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\", \"score\": 0.9961010244449675, \"rank\": 0.003914237070065629, \"text\": \"Gibson\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this remarkable biography\", \"from\": 9392, \"to\": 9417}, {\"ngram\": \"Brown\", \"from\": 9419, \"to\": 9424}, {\"ngram\": \"a compelling answer\", \"from\": 9434, \"to\": 9453}, {\"ngram\": \"the consequences\", \"from\": 9478, \"to\": 9494}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 9527, \"to\": 9534}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the '50s, Gibson was often the only Black woman on the court, and she struggled to afford expensive rackets and clothes.\", \"from\": 9558, \"to\": 9681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9571, \"end\": 9577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\", \"score\": 0.9961010244449675, \"rank\": 0.003914237070065629, \"text\": \"Gibson\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"50s\", \"from\": 9566, \"to\": 9569}, {\"ngram\": \"the only Black woman\", \"from\": 9588, \"to\": 9608}, {\"ngram\": \"the court\", \"from\": 9612, \"to\": 9621}, {\"ngram\": \"expensive rackets\", \"from\": 9651, \"to\": 9668}, {\"ngram\": \"clothes\", \"from\": 9673, \"to\": 9680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She frequently dealt with racism and misogyny, in person and in the press: Reporters called her \\\"arrogant,\\\" \\\"non-cooperative,\\\" and \\\"ungracious.\\\"\", \"from\": 9682, \"to\": 9826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"racism\", \"from\": 9708, \"to\": 9714}, {\"ngram\": \"misogyny\", \"from\": 9719, \"to\": 9727}, {\"ngram\": \"person\", \"from\": 9732, \"to\": 9738}, {\"ngram\": \"the press\", \"from\": 9746, \"to\": 9755}, {\"ngram\": \"Reporters\", \"from\": 9757, \"to\": 9766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Magazines criticized her as insufficiently feminine, photographing her to accentuate her muscles.\", \"from\": 9827, \"to\": 9924, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Magazines\", \"from\": 9827, \"to\": 9836}, {\"ngram\": \"her muscles\", \"from\": 9912, \"to\": 9923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Few brands were willing to sponsor her.\", \"from\": 9925, \"to\": 9964, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Few brands\", \"from\": 9925, \"to\": 9935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As an amateur athlete until shortly before her retirement, she also could not collect money from her sport.\", \"from\": 9965, \"to\": 10072, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an amateur athlete\", \"from\": 9968, \"to\": 9986}, {\"ngram\": \"her retirement\", \"from\": 10008, \"to\": 10022}, {\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 10051, \"to\": 10056}, {\"ngram\": \"her sport\", \"from\": 10062, \"to\": 10071}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This richly detailed biography cements Gibson as one of the most important athletes of the 20th century, while exploring what happens after a star leaves the spotlight.\", \"from\": 10073, \"to\": 10241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10112, \"end\": 10118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\", \"score\": 0.9961010244449675, \"rank\": 0.003914237070065629, \"text\": \"Gibson\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gibson_(guitar_company)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This richly detailed biography\", \"from\": 10073, \"to\": 10103}, {\"ngram\": \"the most important athletes\", \"from\": 10129, \"to\": 10156}, {\"ngram\": \"the 20th century\", \"from\": 10160, \"to\": 10176}, {\"ngram\": \"a star\", \"from\": 10213, \"to\": 10219}, {\"ngram\": \"the spotlight\", \"from\": 10227, \"to\": 10240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read: A century ago, the Paris 1924 Summer Olympics Mind Game: An Inside Look at the Mental Health Playbook of Elite Athletes, by Julie Kliegman At the Tokyo Olympics in 2021, whenSimone Biles pulledout of several of her eventsbecause she had the \\\"twisties\\\"-a phenomenon where gymnasts lose track of themselves in the air-she opened up a wide-ranging conversation about mental health in sports.\", \"from\": 10243, \"to\": 10641, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An Inside Look\", \"from\": 10306, \"to\": 10320}, {\"ngram\": \"the Mental Health Playbook\", \"from\": 10324, \"to\": 10350}, {\"ngram\": \"Elite Athletes\", \"from\": 10354, \"to\": 10368}, {\"ngram\": \"Julie Kliegman\", \"from\": 10373, \"to\": 10387}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 10391, \"to\": 10409}, {\"ngram\": \"her eventsbecause\", \"from\": 10460, \"to\": 10477}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"twisties\\\"-a phenomenon\", \"from\": 10486, \"to\": 10513}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnasts\", \"from\": 10520, \"to\": 10528}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 10534, \"to\": 10539}, {\"ngram\": \"the air\", \"from\": 10557, \"to\": 10564}, {\"ngram\": \"a wide-ranging conversation\", \"from\": 10579, \"to\": 10606}, {\"ngram\": \"mental health\", \"from\": 10613, \"to\": 10626}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 10630, \"to\": 10636}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That conversation, the journalist Kliegman writes inMind Game, was at least a century in the making: Exactly 100 years before Biles's decision, Babe Ruth sat for psychological tests at Columbia University.\", \"from\": 10642, \"to\": 10847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10786, \"end\": 10795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Babe_Ruth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.761339457578978e-32, \"text\": \"Babe Ruth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Babe_Ruth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Babe_Ruth\"}, {\"begin\": 10827, \"end\": 10846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbia_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.611864498452382e-19, \"text\": \"Columbia University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbia_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Columbia_University\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That conversation\", \"from\": 10642, \"to\": 10659}, {\"ngram\": \"the journalist Kliegman\", \"from\": 10661, \"to\": 10684}, {\"ngram\": \"Game\", \"from\": 10699, \"to\": 10703}, {\"ngram\": \"at least a century\", \"from\": 10709, \"to\": 10727}, {\"ngram\": \"the making\", \"from\": 10731, \"to\": 10741}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles's decision\", \"from\": 10768, \"to\": 10784}, {\"ngram\": \"psychological tests\", \"from\": 10804, \"to\": 10823}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports psychology is an old field, but it had its share of fits and starts, as Kliegman documents in her book.\", \"from\": 10848, \"to\": 10958, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sports psychology\", \"from\": 10848, \"to\": 10865}, {\"ngram\": \"an old field\", \"from\": 10869, \"to\": 10881}, {\"ngram\": \"its share\", \"from\": 10894, \"to\": 10903}, {\"ngram\": \"fits\", \"from\": 10907, \"to\": 10911}, {\"ngram\": \"starts\", \"from\": 10916, \"to\": 10922}, {\"ngram\": \"Kliegman documents\", \"from\": 10927, \"to\": 10945}, {\"ngram\": \"her book\", \"from\": 10949, \"to\": 10957}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps most strikingly, the baseball team the St. Louis Browns hired a hypnotist named David F. Tracy in 1950 to improve the performance of its players.\", \"from\": 10959, \"to\": 11112, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11053, \"end\": 11055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Reporter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.383319381154598e-41, \"text\": \"F.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Reporter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Reporter\"}, {\"begin\": 11056, \"end\": 11061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spencer_Tracy\", \"score\": 0.999999998624844, \"rank\": 1.3750589231526169e-09, \"text\": \"Tracy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spencer_Tracy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spencer_Tracy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the baseball team\", \"from\": 10984, \"to\": 11001}, {\"ngram\": \"the St. Louis Browns\", \"from\": 11002, \"to\": 11022}, {\"ngram\": \"a hypnotist\", \"from\": 11029, \"to\": 11040}, {\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 11081, \"to\": 11096}, {\"ngram\": \"its players\", \"from\": 11100, \"to\": 11111}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For decades, officials hardly took seriously the mental health of their elite athletes; tellingly, doctors who had trained in psychology rather than exercise science did not start working for sports teams and leagues until the 1980s.\", \"from\": 11113, \"to\": 11346, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 11117, \"to\": 11124}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 11126, \"to\": 11135}, {\"ngram\": \"the mental health\", \"from\": 11158, \"to\": 11175}, {\"ngram\": \"their elite athletes\", \"from\": 11179, \"to\": 11199}, {\"ngram\": \"doctors\", \"from\": 11212, \"to\": 11219}, {\"ngram\": \"psychology\", \"from\": 11239, \"to\": 11249}, {\"ngram\": \"exercise science\", \"from\": 11262, \"to\": 11278}, {\"ngram\": \"sports teams\", \"from\": 11305, \"to\": 11317}, {\"ngram\": \"leagues\", \"from\": 11322, \"to\": 11329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only in the past 10 years or so have leagues and the public really seemed ready to have a conversation about the intense toll that competing in front of the world can take on a person's psyche.\", \"from\": 11347, \"to\": 11540, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the past 10 years\", \"from\": 11355, \"to\": 11372}, {\"ngram\": \"leagues\", \"from\": 11384, \"to\": 11391}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 11396, \"to\": 11406}, {\"ngram\": \"a conversation\", \"from\": 11435, \"to\": 11449}, {\"ngram\": \"the intense toll\", \"from\": 11456, \"to\": 11472}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 11491, \"to\": 11496}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 11500, \"to\": 11509}, {\"ngram\": \"a person's psyche\", \"from\": 11522, \"to\": 11539}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When an athlete steps into the spotlight, you will, after readingMind Game, have a small window into what they might be feeling and how they handle that pressure.\", \"from\": 11541, \"to\": 11703, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 11546, \"to\": 11556}, {\"ngram\": \"the s